-- 
Zimbabwe Tobacco Industry to Climb to About 63,733 Farmers, Herald Reports

-- B y   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-05-30T07:20:50Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/zimbabwe-tobacco-industry-to-climb-to-about-63-733-farmers-herald-reports.html
About 63,733 farmers may grow tobacco
during  Zimbabwe ’s 2011-2012 farming season from about 53,065
this year, the state-controlled  Herald  said, citing a statement
from the government’s Tobacco Industry and Marketing Board.  Most of the new growers of the leaves will farm on small-
scale plots, the Harare-based Herald said. The TIMB has
registered 4,025 medium-scale growers and 1,697 large-scale
tobacco farmers,  Farmers in the southern African nation have sold about 95
million kilograms (209 million pounds) of tobacco since
February, the Herald said. The country expects to sell between
170 million kilograms and 200 million kilograms of mainly flue-
cured tobacco this year, it added.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
